'''David Adler''' is an American media and event entrepreneur.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Heil|first1=Emily|title=The pre-game for White House correspondents’ dinner: Bloody Marys and brunch selfies with Helen Mirren|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/reliable-source/wp/2016/04/30/the-pre-game-for-white-house-correspondents-dinner-bloody-marys-and-brunch-selfies-with-helen-mirren/|accessdate=21 June 2016|work=[[The Washington Post]]|date=30 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=BizBash and Events DC Honor Five Event Industry Veterans|url=http://www.washingtonspeakers.com/blog/bizbash-and-events-dc-honor-five-event-industry-veterans/|accessdate=21 June 2016|work=Washington Speakers Bureau}}</ref>
==Career== David Adler graduated from [[American University]].<ref>{{cite web|title=American University Alumni Association - Community Home|url=http://alumniassociation.american.edu/s/1395/index1col-social.aspx?sid=1395&gid=1&pgid=2224|publisher=[[American University]] Alumni Association|accessdate=21 June 2016}}</ref> In 1975, Adler founded ''Washington Dossier'', a magazine that featured power, society, politics & history of Washington D.C.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Roberts|first1=Roxanne|title=For lawyers and lobbyists at gift season, it’s never just the thought that counts|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/for-lawyers-and-lobbyists-at-gift-season-its-never-just-the-thought-that-counts/2014/12/19/a0834fe8-85ec-11e4-b9b7-b8632ae73d25_story.html|accessdate=22 June 2016|work=[[The Washington Post]]|date=19 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=The Republished Washington Dossier Library 1975-1991 (in process)|journal=Washington Dossier|date=9 October 2011|url=http://www.washingtondossier.com/?p=56|accessdate=21 June 2016}}</ref> Later he founded BizBash, which originated as an idea and resource marketplace for event organizers of all types from corporate and association to high-end personal and social events. His site has become the largest media property in the B-to-B event industry with nearly 1.5 million annual user sessions.<ref>{{cite news|title=Event Technology Awards Judge's Spotlight – David Adler, BizBash - Event Industry News|url=http://www.eventindustrynews.co.uk/event-technology-news/event-technology-awards-judges-spotlight-david-adler-bizbash/|accessdate=21 June 2016|work=Event Industry News UK|date=23 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Doug A. Sandler Best Selling Author|first1=Speaker|title=Forget Content, Contact is King|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/doug-a-sandler/forget-content-contact-is_b_9194744.html|accessdate=21 June 2016|work=[[The Huffington Post]]|date=10 February 2016}}</ref>
David appeared as a guest speaker at WedTech Summit 2015, a wedding conference uniting brands based in Kensington Park Hotel, San Francisco.<ref>{{cite web|title=Speaker Spotlight: David Adler|url=http://www.wedtechsummit.com/Post/25/Speaker-Spotlight-David-Adler|publisher=WedTech Summit|accessdate=21 June 2016}}</ref> In 2016, The Garden Brunch of the [[White House Correspondents' Association|White House Correspondents' Dinner]] was partly hosted by David Adler.<ref>{{cite news|title=White House Correspondents' Dinner welcomes plenty of big business names at its events, from Sheila Johnson to Kevin Plank - Washington Business Journal|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/washington/blog/2016/05/a-healthy-mix-of-business-and-politicsaround-the.html|accessdate=21 June 2016|work=[[Washington Business Journal]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Heil|first1=Emily|title=Worlds collide at the pre-correspondents’ dinner ‘garden brunch’|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/reliable-source/wp/2015/04/25/worlds-collide-at-the-pre-correspondents-dinner-garden-brunch/|accessdate=21 June 2016|work=[[The Washington Post]]|date=25 April 2015}}</ref>
==Institutional positions== * Advisory Board member of The Event Leadership Institute.<ref>{{cite web|title=Advisory Board of the Events Leadership Institute|url=http://www.eventleadershipinstitute.com/advisoryboard.aspx|publisher=Events Leadership Institute|accessdate=21 June 2016}}</ref> * Founder of BizBash Media.<ref>{{cite news|title=BizBash Names David Micciulla Chief Operating Officer and Chief Financial Officer of BizBash Media: Business Wire|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20070703005159/en/BizBash-Names-David-Micciulla-Chief-Operating-Officer|accessdate=21 June 2016|work=[[Business Wire]]}}</ref> * Director at Society for Independent Show Organizers A.K.A ''SISO''.<ref>{{cite web|title=SISO Board|url=http://www.siso.org/about-siso/siso-board|publisher=Society of Independent Show Organizers|accessdate=21 June 2016}}</ref>
